## 📊 Market Analysis

### Total Addressable Market (TAM)
- **Global Social Media Management Software Market**: $17.7B (2024)
- **Projected CAGR**: 18.2% (2024-2030)
- **Market by 2030**: $46.8B

### Serviceable Addressable Market (SAM)
- **SMBs in US, EU, UK**: ~32M businesses
- **Social media active businesses**: ~18M (56%)
- **Paying for social tools**: ~4M (22%)
- **Market value at $50 ARPU**: $2.4B

### Serviceable Obtainable Market (SOM)
- **Year 1 Target**: 1,000 paying customers
- **Year 3 Target**: 10,000 paying customers
- **Year 5 Target**: 50,000 paying customers

### Competitive Landscape
**Competitors**: Hootsuite ($739M revenue), Buffer ($20M), Sprout Social ($306M), Later ($25M)

**Our Advantage**:
- ✅ AI-first approach (viral prediction, content generation)
- ✅ More affordable pricing (50% cheaper than Hootsuite)
- ✅ Modern tech stack (faster, more reliable)
- ✅ Better UX (Tron-inspired, intuitive)
- ✅ Bleeding-edge AI (Gemini, GPT-4, RAG)

